The paper deals with the problem of sparse signal recovery in a streaming system, which involves processing measurements over a sliding interval and estimating sparse coefficients by solving a weighted L1-norm minimization program. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), scientific computing (cs.SI), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
